rComments: Excellent teacher. I learned so many things in immigration law.

I was very surprised to read negative comments on here about this prof. I personally found him to be one of the best law professors I've ever had! Not only is he very kind and approachable, he truly wants his students to succeed and is very passionate about the topics he teaches. I recommend this prof without hesitation :)
Quite theatrical in his way of lecturing but good prof that really cares about his students. Exam and marking was fair.

This professor's strong grasp of immigration and environment law feeds into his constitutional law course. He's also more likely than other profs to bring up glaring social justice issues, such as the Omar Khadr case or the torture of Afghan detainees. Respect.
He makes everything so complicated and can't finish a sentence. I can't believe I paid to listen to him. Brutal.

Very frustrating that he is teaching a class on the foundation of our legal system.  His powerpoints are useless, littered with impertinent information. His lectures are confusing and unstructured. He prefers attempting to make eloquent sentences than convey the information effectively.  Everyone in class was lost throughout the entire semester.
Really bad teacher - did not understand the class at all (legislation)

Monsieur LeBouthillier did a really great job of confusing students, bringing up irrelevant points in class, making available complicated PowerPoints with illogical case citations that made learning administrative law much more difficult than it had to be. Unable to provide comprehensible, logical answers to student questions. Avoid at all costs!
